00:18:30.640 --> 00:18:32.470
to just search
course descriptions.

00:18:32.470 --> 00:18:35.470
And this was an effort that
arose out of our friends

00:18:35.470 --> 00:18:37.930
in the Safra Center
for Ethics just wanting

00:18:37.930 --> 00:18:41.260
to know, where are
people teaching ethics?

00:18:41.260 --> 00:18:44.440
And so we are able to, again,
work with folks at HUIT to be

00:18:44.440 --> 00:18:48.220
able to import all of the course
description information that we

00:18:48.220 --> 00:18:51.040
could get, also grab some
of that information for some

00:18:51.040 --> 00:18:54.310
of the other schools that aren't
on my.Harvard and put it in one

00:18:54.310 --> 00:18:57.470
place, make it searchable,
and do all sorts of--

00:18:57.470 --> 00:19:01.310
be able to make nice
plots of different things.

00:19:01.310 --> 00:19:06.570
A challenge of-- it's
not really a challenge.

00:19:06.570 --> 00:19:09.470
It's just sort of a
reality, is that we

00:19:09.470 --> 00:19:12.667
are a little bit spread out
in terms of our data systems.

00:19:12.667 --> 00:19:13.250
And that's OK.

