you can really quickly come

01:01:42.610 --> 01:01:46.130
to understand that you need to
be able to define the problem,

01:01:46.130 --> 01:01:46.630
right.

01:01:46.630 --> 01:01:48.490
There's a set of
competencies, here,

01:01:48.490 --> 01:01:50.800
that each of these
students need to get.

01:01:50.800 --> 01:01:53.620
You need to understand the
root causes of those problems.

01:01:53.620 --> 01:01:56.890
You need to be able
to iterate and think

01:01:56.890 --> 01:02:00.130
in an iterative learning way
about potential solutions

01:02:00.130 --> 01:02:02.440
and make selections
about those solutions.

01:02:02.440 --> 01:02:04.921
And you need to understand your
own role as a social change

01:02:04.921 --> 01:02:05.420
maker.

01:02:05.420 --> 01:02:07.150
And so despite the
fact that they're

01:02:07.150 --> 01:02:09.790
all across different
schools, and potentially

01:02:09.790 --> 01:02:13.089
different in many ways, there's
actually a lot of similarities.

01:02:13.089 --> 01:02:15.130
And that's what we wanted
to start to understand.

01:02:15.130 --> 01:02:17.900
This is a set of keywords.

01:02:17.900 --> 01:02:20.980
So we followed, again, on the
coattails of the ethics folks

01:02:20.980 --> 01:02:23.920
and did this iterative process
of looking for keywords

01:02:23.920 --> 01:02:25.065
in the course descriptions.

01:02:25.065 --> 01:02:27.190
We would have loved to have
been able to drill down

01:02:27.190 --> 01:02:29.470
to the level of the
syllabi, because we suspect

01:02:29.470 --> 01:02:31.780
that when we talk about
the competencies required

01:02:31.780 --> 01:02:33.280
to be an effective
social innovator,

01:02:33.280 --> 01:02:36.700
it might be happening
at that syllabus level.

01:02:36.700 --> 01:02:38.987
And when we get there,
we will do that.

01:02:38.987 --> 01:02:40.570
But in the meantime,
it just gives you

01:02:40.570 --> 01:02:45.100
a sense of the range of search
terms that came up for us.

01:02:45.100 --> 01:02:48.310
And then we would feed
those back in to the system

01:02:48.310 --> 01:02:51.730
until we came to this 521.

01:02:51.730 --> 01:02:55.440
And so yeah, for
next year, I mean,

01:02:55.440 --> 01:02:57.030
in terms of what
kind of resources

01:02:57.030 --> 01:02:59.280
can we use to support
students and faculty

01:02:59.280 --> 01:03:01.950
in creating a community
and finding their way--

01:03:01.950 --> 01:03:05.037
we've been thinking about
a compendium of curricula.

01:03:05.037 --> 01:03:07.620
We think that just would be an
interesting contribution, also,

01:03:07.620 --> 01:03:08.850
beyond Harvard.

01:03:08.850 --> 01:03:12.460
And that that would then draw
folks into the conversation,

01:03:12.460 --> 01:03:13.122
broadly.

01:03:13.122 --> 01:03:14.580
Oh, this is our
big takeaway, which

01:03:14.580 --> 01:03:17.940
is that pretty much every single
school is offering courses

01:03:17.940 --> 01:03:18.570
on this front.

01:03:18.570 --> 01:03:20.580
I mean, and it's really
pretty well distributed.

01:03:20.580 --> 01:03:21.996
There's an other
group, here, that

01:03:21.996 --> 01:03:23.460
represents a couple
of the schools,

01:03:23.460 --> 01:03:26.430
but, again, this, just like
Erin said about the other,

01:03:26.430 --> 01:03:28.200
this is our first
cut at a snapshot.

01:03:28.200 --> 01:03:31.720
We're still trying to figure
out even what the bounds are.

01:03:31.720 --> 01:03:33.630
And so a step for us--

01:03:33.630 --> 01:03:35.864
next step for us will
also be connecting

01:03:35.864 --> 01:03:36.780
with relevant faculty.

01:03:36.780 --> 01:03:39.120
Faculty are interested
in this work,

01:03:39.120 --> 01:03:42.180
particularly faculty who have an
experiential learning pedagogy.

01:03:42.180 --> 01:03:44.120
They seem to be
very drawn to this.

01:03:44.120 --> 01:03:46.980
And ask them for
reactions to the set

01:03:46.980 --> 01:03:49.096
of courses we've surfaced.

01:03:49.096 --> 01:03:50.970
And then eventually just
make recommendations

01:03:50.970 --> 01:03:54.040
to improve the student pathway
for making social impact.

01:03:54.040 --> 01:03:55.740
I mean, many of them
come here and say

01:03:55.740 --> 01:03:58.660
that's why they're
getting an education, now.

01:03:58.660 --> 01:04:01.530
And so how can we prepare
them to do that well?

01:04:01.530 --> 01:04:04.050
And then hopes-- yeah, I
mean, just that, again,

01:04:04.050 --> 01:04:06.870
the multi-disciplinary
learning journey in particular

01:04:06.870 --> 01:04:09.780
could be a little
easier for students.

01:04:09.780 --> 01:04:11.010
Right now, we're very siloed.

01:04:11.010 --> 01:04:12.780
I think we all know that.

01:04:12.780 --> 01:04:15.810
And they feel it the most.

01:04:15.810 --> 01:04:18.242
And then creating connection
between faculty and students

01:04:18.242 --> 01:04:20.200
who would benefit from
working with each other.

01:04:20.200 --> 01:04:21.699
I mean, even on
this project, I feel

01:04:21.699 --> 01:04:24.110
like I've connected with
some of you who might not

01:04:24.110 --> 01:04:26.312
have identified as falling
into social innovation,

01:04:26.312 --> 01:04:28.020
but when we get down
to the nitty gritty,

01:04:28.020 --> 01:04:29.811
I think we're actually
grappling with a lot

01:04:29.811 --> 01:04:32.640
of similar questions.

01:04:32.640 --> 01:04:35.700
And this idea of
developing a one Harvard

01:04:35.700 --> 01:04:38.160
ecosystem, especially
when resources

01:04:38.160 --> 01:04:39.420
are distributed across school.

01:04:39.420 --> 01:04:42.720
So the Kennedy School cannot
own social innovation.

01:04:42.720 --> 01:04:43.950
And we know that.

01:04:43.950 --> 01:04:46.140
But Harvard as a
whole, really could

01:04:46.140 --> 01:04:49.230
be a dominant player in this
space, if we could coordinate.

01:04:49.230 --> 01:04:53.100
So there are certain topics
where no department, no school

01:04:53.100 --> 01:04:55.410
is going to be able to
really shape a field,

01:04:55.410 --> 01:04:57.800
but together we might be
able to do quite a bit.

01:04:57.800 --> 01:05:00.250
So that's where I'm at.

